params.name: s
params.description: sequence number, used for resuming sessions and heartbeats

params.name: t
params.description: the event name for this payload

params.name: encoding
params.description: The encoding of received gateway packets

params.name: compress
params.description: whether this connection supports compression of packets

params.name: large_threshold
params.description: value between 50 and 250, total number of members where the gateway will stop sending offline members in the guild member

params.name: presence
params.description: presence structure for initial presence information

params.name: guild_id
params.description: id of the guild to get members for

params.name: query
params.description: string that username starts with, or an empty string to return all members

params.name: limit
params.description: maximum number of members to send matching the `query`; a limit of `0` can be used with an empty string `query` to return all members

params.name: presences
params.description: used to specify if we want the presences of the matched members

params.name: user_ids
params.description: used to specify which users you wish to fetch

params.name: nonce
params.description: nonce to identify the [Guild Members Chunk](#DOCS_TOPICS_GATEWAY/guild-members-chunk) response

params.name: channel_id
params.description: id of the voice channel client wants to join (null if disconnecting)

params.name: since
params.description: unix time (in milliseconds) of when the client went idle, or null if the client is not idle

params.name: afk
params.description: whether or not the client is afk

params.name: heartbeat_interval
params.description: the interval (in milliseconds) the client should heartbeat with

params.name: user
params.description: information about the user including email

params.name: guilds
params.description: the guilds the user is in

params.name: shard
params.description: the [shard information](#DOCS_TOPICS_GATEWAY/sharding) associated with this session, if sent when identifying

params.name: channel_ids
params.description: the parent channel ids whose threads are being synced.  If omitted, then threads were synced for the entire guild.  This  may contain channel_ids that have no active threads as well, so you know to clear that data.

params.name: threads
params.description: all active threads in the given channels that the current user can access

params.name: members
params.description: all thread member objects from the synced threads for the current user, indicating which threads the current user has been added to

name: Thread Member Update Event Extra Fields

params.name: member_count
params.description: the approximate number of members in the thread, capped at 50

params.name: added_members
params.description: the users who were added to the thread

params.name: removed_member_ids
params.description: the id of the users who were removed from the thread

params.name: last_pin_timestamp
params.description: the time at which the most recent pinned message was pinned

params.name: guild_id
params.description: id of the guild whose integrations were updated

params.name: nick
params.description: nickname of the user in the guild

params.name: joined_at
params.description: when the user joined the guild

params.name: premium_since
params.description: when the user starting [boosting](https://support.discord.com/hc/en-us/articles/360028038352-Server-Boosting-) the guild

params.name: deaf
params.description: whether the user is deafened in voice channels

params.name: mute
params.description: whether the user is muted in voice channels

params.name: pending
params.description: whether the user has not yet passed the guild's [Membership Screening](#DOCS_RESOURCES_GUILD/membership-screening-object) requirements

params.name: communication_disabled_until
params.description: when the user's [timeout](https://support.discord.com/hc/en-us/articles/4413305239191-Time-Out-FAQ) will expire and the user will be able to communicate in the guild again, null or a time in the past if the user is not timed out

params.name: chunk_index
params.description: the chunk index in the expected chunks for this response (0 <= chunk\_index < chunk\_count)

params.name: chunk_count
params.description: the total number of expected chunks for this response

params.name: not_found
params.description: if passing an invalid id to `REQUEST_GUILD_MEMBERS`, it will be returned here

params.name: presences
params.description: if passing true to `REQUEST_GUILD_MEMBERS`, presences of the returned members will be here

params.name: nonce
params.description: the nonce used in the [Guild Members Request](#DOCS_TOPICS_GATEWAY/request-guild-members)
